R

randgen - Class in drsa
This application implements the Pseudo-random Byte Generator (drsa.PRBG).
It may do one of two things:
- Perform benchmarking of the drsa.PRBG setup - uses random passwords and multiple confusion strings and iteration counters to test the setup of the generator, and produces a histogram with the processing time per confusion string size [1-4], for each iteration count {1, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 200}.
randgen() - Constructor for class drsa.randgen
 
randomString(int) - Static method in class drsa.utils.Utils
Uses the Java SecureRandom class to produce random alphabetic strings with the given length.
reseed(byte[]) - Method in class drsa.PRBG
Resseeds the generator
